вҠў context
  yield schema вүЎ cells(id, program_id, name, body_type[soft|stem|hard], body, state[declared|computing|frozen|bottom]), givens(cell_id, source_cell, source_field, is_optional), yields(cell_id, field_name, value_text, is_frozen), oracles(cell_id, oracle_type[deterministic|semantic], assertion, condition_expr[not_empty|is_json_array|length_matches:CELL]), cell_claims(cell_id, piston_id), ready_cells VIEW
  yield syntax вүЎ вҠў NAME = cell, given XвҶ’Y = dependency, yield NAME = output, yield NAME вүЎ VALUE = hard literal, вҲҙ TEXT = soft body, вҲҙвҲҙ TEXT = stem body (permanently soft), вҠў= TEXT = hard computed, вҠЁ TEXT = oracle, вҠўвҲҳ NAME Г— N = iteration (expands to N chained cells)

вҠў pour
  given contextвҶ’schema
  given contextвҶ’syntax
  yield description
  вҲҙвҲҙ Describe how the Cell pour operation works: given В«syntaxВ» as input and В«schemaВ» as the target, explain the parsing rules that transform turnstyle syntax into SQL INSERT statements. Cover cell types, ID conventions, oracle classification, and iteration expansion. This is the stem cell that defines how .cell programs become data in Dolt.
